==Controversy about classification as submunition vs cluster munition==
Various human rights organizations, such as "Aktionsbündnis Landmine.de" and [[Handicap International]] view the SMArt 155 as a cluster munition. Germany’s representatives managed to ensure that SMArt 155 did not meet criteria for cluster munition of the [[Convention on Cluster Munitions|Oslo Agreement on the Prohibition of Cluster Bombs]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Nagel |first=Sarah |title=Riestern für die Rüstungsindustrie (nd-aktuell.de) |language=de |work=Neues Deutschland |url=https://www.nd-aktuell.de/artikel/209157.riestern-fuer-die-ruestungsindustrie.html |access-date=2023-03-22 |archive-date=2023-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322221726/https://www.nd-aktuell.de/artikel/209157.riestern-fuer-die-ruestungsindustrie.html |url-status=live }}</ref>  Critics view this exempting definition in contradiction to the United Nations' understanding of cluster munitions.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Zumach |first=Andreas |date=2009-03-02 |title=Rüstungsfirma Diehl: Waffen bauen, Sprache säubern |language=de |work=Die Tageszeitung: taz |url=https://taz.de/!5167001/ |access-date=2023-03-22 |issn=0931-9085 |archive-date=2023-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322221727/https://taz.de/!5167001/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Critics also point out the similar effects of cluster munitions on the civilian population as in the case of [[unexploded ordnance]] or mistargeting.<ref>{{Cite web  |title=Alternative cluster munitions - problem or solution?  |url=https://www.landmine.de/fileadmin/user_upload/pdf/Publi/alternative_streumunition.pdf  |access-date=2023-03-22  |archive-date=2022-01-29  |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220129003158/https://www.landmine.de/fileadmin/user_upload/pdf/Publi/alternative_streumunition.pdf  |url-status=dead  }}</ref>

In July 2008, the journalist Stefan Aigner wrote: " Today, Diehl is one of the most successful German arms producers. According to its own information, around one third of its profit of 2.3 billion euros comes from armaments production. Among other things, cluster munitions are produced."  Diehl’s lawyers demanded a cease-and-desist declaration from Aigner. The lawyers referred to the exceptions made in the Oslo Agreement, which allegedly pose no danger to civilians. In the trial before the Munich Regional Court, Aigner and Diehl reached a [[settlement (law)|settlement]] on March 2, 2009, after the judge made it clear that he would accept Diehl’s claim.  The settlement includes that Diehl s ammunition may not be referred to as cluster munitions.<ref name="taz">{{Cite news |last=Zumach |first=Andreas |date=2009-03-04 |title=Streit über Rüstungsbegriff: Vergleich im Prozess um "Streumunition" |language=de |work=Die Tageszeitung: taz |url=https://taz.de/!5166905/ |access-date=2023-03-22 |issn=0931-9085 |archive-date=2023-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322221724/https://taz.de/!5166905/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Duwe |first=Silvio |title=Punktzielmunition trifft Pressefreiheit |language=de |url=https://www.telepolis.de/features/Punktzielmunition-trifft-Pressefreiheit-3422003.html |access-date=2023-03-22 |archive-date=2023-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322221724/https://www.telepolis.de/features/Punktzielmunition-trifft-Pressefreiheit-3422003.html |url-status=live }}</ref> In return, Diehl assumed the costs of the proceedings.

"Intelligent Working System" came in third place in the election for [[Unwort des Jahres]] 2009.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Stefan Aigner |date=2010-01-10 |title=Intelligenter bomben mit blöden Worten |language=de-DE |url=https://www.regensburg-digital.de/intelligenter-bomben-mit-bloden-worten/20012010/ |access-date=2023-03-22 |archive-date=2023-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322221724/https://www.regensburg-digital.de/intelligenter-bomben-mit-bloden-worten/20012010/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Behind the harmless term "intelligent active systems" the jury saw technologically advanced types of ammunition, which are produced by a subsidiary of two armaments companies with the equally disguised company name "Gesellschaft für Intelligente Wirksysteme mbH".<ref>{{Cite news |date=2010-01-19 |title=Sprachforscher: "Betriebsratsverseucht" ist Unwort des Jahres |language=de |work=FAZ.NET |url=https://www.faz.net/aktuell/gesellschaft/sprachforscher-betriebsratsverseucht-ist-unwort-des-jahres-1581819.html |access-date=2023-03-22 |issn=0174-4909 |archive-date=2023-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322221724/https://www.faz.net/aktuell/gesellschaft/sprachforscher-betriebsratsverseucht-ist-unwort-des-jahres-1581819.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

